observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our prior year’s audit recommendation with modification that the Local Chief Executive:
Enjoin the Inventory Committee to expedite the One-Time Cleansing of the PPE account in accordance with the procedures outlined in COA Circular No. 2020-006, to ensure that the PPE balances are fairly presented in the financial statements;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to complete the Property Ledger Cards;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to draw necessary correcting entries for the erroneous depreciation; and
Direct the Supply Officer to:
Update the Property Cards;
Delist the items in the RPCPPE which cost do not meet the capitalization threshold of P50,000.00 and subsequently, issue corresponding Inventory Custodian Slip (ICSs) for delisted items in the RPCPPE.

We recommended that management:
Direct the MEED Officer to submit proposal for the procurement and installation of computerized billing and collection system for the MEEDO;
Enjoin the Sangguniang Bayan to support funding initiatives based on the submitted proposal of the MEED Officer;
Direct the MEED Officer to submit Report to the Municipal Accountant on the Lopez Jaena Water System Receivables as of every month end as basis for the recording;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to record the receivables from Lopez Jaena Water System subscribers and maintain subsidiary ledger for every account; and
For the subsequent issuance of Financial Statements, require the Municipal Accountant to disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements relevant information regarding the Lopez Jaena Water System receivables.

We recommended that the management direct the LDRRMO to include and implement in the LDRRM Investment Plan the deficiencies noted relative to compliance on the minimum standards for disaster preparedness. Likewise, we enjoin collaborative discussion thereon with the Sangguniang Bayan on the implementation and augmentation of the LDRRM Fund. The following were still not fully implemented:

1. Recovery Plan/Business Continuity Planning/Communication Advocacy Plan;
2. Pre-disaster Recovery Planning;
3. Database Management; 
3. Management of the Dead and Missing; and
4. 500 food packs and hygiene kits as minimum standby/stock

We have recommended that the LCE direct the officials concerned to stop the act of splitting government contracts and strictly adhere to the provisions of R.A. No. 9184 in all procurements;
Ensure consistency of the mode of procurement as reflected in the RFQs and BAC recommendation; and
Justify why Management resorted to Small Value Procurement or Shopping instead of going through the process of public bidding.

