We have reiterated our prior year’s recommendation to management that:

a.	The municipality shall prioritize the attendance of the property officer or any one  in his/her behalf in trainings and seminars on property disposals;

b.	The Property Officer shall file an application for disposal of unserviceable properties together with the duly accomplished Inventory and Inspection Report on Unserviceable Properties for appraisal by the COA Technical Audit Specialist;

c.	The management shall prepare and accomplish Waste Materials Report;

d.	The Mayor is advised to create an Appraisal and Disposal Committee to assess the remaining scrap value of the unserviceable properties and to recommend to him the mode of disposal appropriate and most advantageous to the government;

e.	To comply with the specific guidelines in the disposal of unserviceable properties provided for under COA Circular No. 89-296 dated January 27, 1989.

We have recommended to management to:

a.	Instruct concerned Municipal Officials to make representations to confirm and document completion/acceptance from the source agency of the programs/ projects;

b.	Require the Municipal Accountant to make representations to verify the ledger balances from the source agency books and extend earnest efforts to reconcile should balances differ;

c.	Direct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to return the unexpended balances of the fund transfers; otherwise, avail of the write-off provision contained under COA Memorandum Circular 2016-005; and

d.	 Instruct the Municipal Accountant to effect adjustments to correct the over and understatements in the accounts affected.

